---
// @run402/astro@0.2.0 workaround — kychee-com/run402-private#407.
//
// The integration's `buildStart` hook bails early on
// `discovery.length === 0` (no source-rewriteable image tags found in any
// `.astro`/`.tsx`/`.jsx`/`.mdx`/`.md` source file) BEFORE running the
// `assetsDir` walk. Kychon's images live in JSONB row configs rendered via
// `src/lib/blocks.ts`, so there are zero static template literals — which
// means without this file the integration loads, scans, finds nothing,
// returns, and never uploads the demo's assets nor writes
// `dist/_assets-manifest.json`.
//
// This file exists ONLY to satisfy the integration's discovery
// precondition. It is never imported, never rendered, never visible in
// the build output. The Astro source-walker (which the scanner uses)
// walks every file under the project root with one of the scanned
// extensions, so the single static reference below is enough — even
// though nothing renders this fragment.
//
// The referenced `_run402-trigger.png` is a 67-byte 1x1 transparent PNG.
// Sub-320px sources emit a one-line build warning and upload a single
// non-variant entry — trivial cost. The manifest gets one harmless extra
// entry that nothing in Kychon ever looks up.
//
// DELETE THIS FILE (and `src/images/_run402-trigger.png`) once #407
// ships in a `@run402/astro` patch release — the data-driven `assetsDir`
// path will run unconditionally and this trigger becomes pointless.
import Image from '@run402/astro/Image.astro';
---
